
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `kerneloops-submit` baraye ersal gozaresh-haye khata (error reports) az هسته (kernel) Linux be server Kerneloops estefade mishavad. In komak mikonad ta توسعه دهندگان (developers) moshkelat ra peyda va rafa konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh version program.
    🔹 `--help`     --> 🆘 Namayesh rahnama (help) estefade az dastoor.
    🔹 `--no-dmesg` --> 🚫 Gozaresh dmesg ra ersal nakonid.
    🔹 `--comment "matn"` --> 💬 Ezafe kardan yek tozih (comment) be gozaresh.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ kerneloops-submit

    🔹 Ersal gozaresh-e akharin crash be server Kerneloops.

    $ kerneloops-submit --comment "In crash dar hengame nasb drayver grafik رخ داد."

    🔹 Ersal gozaresh crash ba yek tozih.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ sudo kerneloops-submit

    🔹 Ersal gozaresh be Kerneloops. estefade az `sudo` lazem ast chon barresi file-haye systemi niaz be dastresi root darad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `kerneloops-submit` command is used to submit kernel oops reports to the Kerneloops server. This helps developers identify and fix kernel problems.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Show program's version number and exit.
    🔹 `--help`     --> 🆘 Show help message and exit.
    🔹 `--no-dmesg` --> 🚫 Do not include the dmesg output in the report.
    🔹 `--comment "text"` --> 💬 Add a comment to the report.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ kerneloops-submit

    🔹 Submit the latest kernel crash report to the Kerneloops server.

    $ kerneloops-submit --comment "This crash occurred during graphics driver installation."

    🔹 Submit crash report with a comment.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ sudo kerneloops-submit

    🔹 Submit the report to Kerneloops. Using `sudo` is often necessary because accessing system files requires root privileges.
